MarlinSpike — Alembic migration directory
==========================================

This directory was initialised by Flask-Migrate / Alembic as part of
v3.5.4.  All schema changes from v3.5.4 onwards are tracked here.

Common operator commands
------------------------

  # See which revision the target DB is at
  python -m marlinspike.db current

  # Advance to the latest migration
  python -m marlinspike.db upgrade

  # Roll back one step
  python -m marlinspike.db downgrade

  # Generate a new auto-detected migration after editing models.py
  python -m marlinspike.db migrate -m "describe the change"

Existing deployments (v3.5.3 and earlier)
------------------------------------------

If you ran any version of MarlinSpike before v3.5.4 the schema was
already created by the legacy db.create_all() + ALTER TABLE path.  Stamp
the database at baseline so Alembic does not try to re-apply it:

  python -m marlinspike.db stamp head

Fresh installs
--------------

Nothing to do.  The first boot of v3.5.4 runs ``upgrade head``
automatically and brings up a fully-initialised schema.

Single-process note
-------------------

The automatic upgrade runs inside create_app().  It is intentionally
skipped when MARLINSPIKE_ALLOW_NO_DATABASE_URL=true (test mode) or when
the migrations/ directory cannot be located (pip-installed deployments
that did not include this tree).
